				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Marscaleb wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Wasn't the MMC3 the most commonly-used mapper though?</div><br />It's one of the most common mappers, yes, but having one entire PRG slot permanently dedicated to audio means you lose 8KB of your addressing space, and there's only 1 switchable slot left for the game engine to use. This makes the engine harder to design, and it will mostly likely perform worse than it would if it could map game code and data more freely. Most programmers aren't willing to make that sacrifice.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

