				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Marscaleb, can you clarify which you mean...PCM samples or DPCM?<br /><br />PCM requires constant input from the main program, but gives the highest quality sound. And, generally not used during regular gameplay.<br /><br />DPCM is an automatic process that allows the main program freedom to do whatever it wants. And is frequently used for background music, sound fx, etc.<br /><br />Because, most of the answers here seem to be specific to PCM use, and not DPCM samples.</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://nesdoug.com" class="postlink">nesdoug.com</a> -- blog/tutorial on programming for the NES</div>
					<br clear="all" /><br />

